{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κρηπίς</b>, ῖδος, ἡ, <br /> <b>man's high boot</b> (compare [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“AB” 273)\">Refs</a>], <b>half-boot</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hegemon Comicus et Parodus “Parod.” 4, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Eq.” 12.10, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Char.” 2.7 (uncertain): distinguished from ὑποδήματα, 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Aristocles Historicus 8; κ. λευκαί, a mark of effeminacy, 4th-3rd c.BC: Timaeus Historicus 82. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__b</b></Level4> κρηπῖδες <b>soldiers' boots</b>, i.e. <b>soldiers</b> themselves, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.6. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>shoeshaped cake</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 6.77. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <b>groundwork, foundation, basement</b> of a building or altar, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.93, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Tr.” 993 (_anapaest meter_), 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 38 (_plural_), “HF” 985, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “An.” 3.4.7, “IG” 12.372.67; κ. καὶ στυλοβάτας [prev. work]42(1).102.7 (Epid.); τύμβου 'πὶ κρηπῖδ᾽ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hel.” 547: _metaphorically_, βάλλεσθαι κρηπῖδα σοφῶν ἐπέων 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.138 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἀοιδᾶν βαλέσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 7.3; ἐβάλοντο φαεννὰν κρηπῖδ᾽ ἐλευθερίας [prev\\. author] “fragment” 77; κ. γένους 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 1261; ἡ ἐγκράτεια ἀρετῆς κ. Xenophon Historicus [{5-6th c.BC}] “Memorabilia” 1.5.4, compare 1st c.AD: Onosander (Onasander) Tacticus 4.4: οὐδέπω κακῶν κ. ὕπεστιν\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>] we have not yet got to the <b>bottom</b> of misery, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Pers.” 815; κ. θαλάσσης Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus [{2-3rd c.AD}] “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 3.453, 5.48 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; κ. καὶ ἕδρα νόσου <b>foundation</b> and seat of disease, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Maximus Tyrius Sophista 13.7. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>walled edge</b> of a river or canal, <b>quay</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.185, 2.170, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 5.37.8, “PTeb.” 382.9 (1st c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>abutment</b> of a bridge, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“epigram Gr.” 1078.3 (from Adana)\">Refs</a>]; <b>tiers</b> of seats in a theatre, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“IG” 11(2).203 A 95 (Delos, 3rd c.BC). \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>ox-tongue, Helminthia echioides</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “HP” 7.8.3, 1st c.AD: Plinius Rerum Naturalium Scriptor “HN” 21.99. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> a bandage, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus “Fasc.” 59. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8094","accentedUnicode":"κρηπίς","shortDef":"a bank; footing","mediumDef":"a bank; footing","stepGloss":"a bank","stepTransliteration":"krēpis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}